# AIESS Mobile App - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is the AIESS Mobile App v1.0 MVP - a React Native/Expo app for Battery Energy Storage System monitoring and control.

## Documentation First
Before implementing ANY feature:
1. Read the relevant section in `docs/PRD.md`
2. Check `docs/api/` for API specifications
3. Use Supabase MCP to verify database schema

## Required Tools - USE THESE!

### Supabase MCP
You have Supabase MCP access. USE IT for:
- `mcp_supabase_list_tables` - Check schema before writing queries
- `mcp_supabase_execute_sql` - Test queries
- `mcp_supabase_search_docs` - Find Supabase documentation
- Project ID: `fcfuuwmzwxltxsgmcqck`

### Task Management
Use the built-in TODO system to:
- Break down features into small tasks
- Track progress
- Mark items complete as you go

## Git Workflow

### Commit Messages
Use conventional commits:
- `feat:` new feature
- `fix:` bug fix
- `docs:` documentation
- `style:` formatting
- `refactor:` code restructure
- `test:` tests

### Commit Frequency
Commit after each logical unit of work. Good commits:
- "feat: implement login screen with email/password"
- "feat: add device list with Supabase query"

### Version Tracking
Update version in `app.json` for milestones:
- v0.1.0 - Auth complete
- v0.2.0 - Devices complete
- v0.3.0 - Monitor complete
- etc.

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Define interfaces for all data structures
- Use strict mode

### React Native
- Functional components only
- Use hooks for state/effects
- Extract reusable logic to custom hooks in `/hooks`

### File Organization
```
app/           # Expo Router screens
components/    # Reusable components
hooks/         # Custom hooks (useAuth, useDevices, etc.)
lib/           # API clients (supabase.ts, influxdb.ts, aws-schedules.ts)
contexts/      # React contexts
types/         # TypeScript interfaces
constants/     # Colors, config values
locales/       # i18n translations (en.json, pl.json)
```

## Key Implementation Details

### Authentication
- Use Supabase Auth
- Store session in Expo SecureStore (NOT AsyncStorage)
- Google sign-in via native SDK
- Apple button visible but disabled (v1.1)

### Live Monitor
- InfluxDB via HTTP POST
- 5-second refresh interval
- Factory Load = max(0, grid + pv - battery)
- Battery: + = charging, - = discharging

### Schedule Rules
- AWS API Gateway with x-api-key header
- Rule schema in `docs/api/RULES_SCHEMA.md`
- Priority P4-P8 for user rules
- Time format: HHMM integer (1430 = 14:30)

### i18n
- Set up from start with i18next
- All user-facing strings must use translation keys
- Support EN (default) and PL

## PRD Updates
If you discover something needs to change in the spec:
1. Update `docs/PRD.md`
2. Commit: `docs: update PRD - [what changed]`

## Testing Setup
Primary testing device: **iPhone 17 via Expo Go**

To test:
```bash
npx expo start
# Scan QR code with iPhone camera
```

Make sure iPhone and dev machine are on same WiFi network.

## Before Marking Feature Complete
- [ ] Works on iPhone via Expo Go (PRIMARY)
- [ ] Works on iOS simulator (optional)
- [ ] Works on Android emulator (optional)
- [ ] Loading states handled
- [ ] Error states handled
- [ ] Empty states handled
- [ ] Uses i18n keys
- [ ] Committed to git
- [ ] Version bumped if milestone

